      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AT THE DISTANCE (5) has been racing well of late. Finished second at his latest appearance over 2190m at Shepparton, beaten a head. Meets a comparable field and he can grab that well-deserved win. MISTA WALKER (7) is in good form at present. Finished third at his latest appearance over 2080m at this track, beaten 9 metres. Has to contend with a very wide draw. Good enough to put himself in the winners' stall. SKYVALLEY BOY (6) is heading the right way, improving last time out to finish second at Bendigo over 2150m. Genuine threat. AGAINST THE BRIDLE (3) was in the money two starts ago then things went amiss last start when he broke and finished a distant fourth over 2080m at this track. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a similar line up so if he behaves a big run is likely.",
